'''syslog-ng''' is a powerful monitoring and logging daemon.

==Installation==
=== USE flags ===
{{USEflag|package=app-admin/syslog-ng|desc=Optional USE flags for {{Package|app-admin/syslog-ng}}
|amqp+++Enable support for AMQP destinations
|caps
|dbi
|geoip
|ipv6
|json
|mongodb
|pacct+++Enable support for reading Process Accounting
|python+yes
|redis+++Build the Redis output module using (requires dev-libs/hiredis)
|smtp
|spoof-source
|tcpd+yes
|systemd
}}

=== Emerge ===
Install {{Package|app-admin/syslog-ng}}:
{{Emerge|syslog-ng}}

{{Note|It is a bad idea to run more than one system logger on a physical host. Other local loggers should be removed or disabled.}}

Add syslog-ng to default run level:
{{RootCmd|rc-update add syslog-ng default}}

== Sources ==
The default source for syslog messages is:
 source src { unix-stream("/dev/log"); internal(); };

If the system is running systemd, this needs to be changed to [http://www.balabit.com/sites/default/files/documents/syslog-ng-pe-latest-guides/en/syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin/html/configuring-sources-journal.html]:
 source src { systemd-journal(); internal(); };

